 {"id":"bd-18e8","title":"Add Configuration Options for Self-Healing Behavior","description":"# Add Configuration Options for Self-Healing Behavior

## Problem Statement
The self-healing features (hook auto-starts daemon, daemon auto-installs hooks) are powerful but may not be desired by all users. Some users may want:
- Full manual control
- Specific behavior combinations
- Different settings for different environments
- Easy CI/CD overrides without config file changes

## Solution: Configuration Options
Add a `[self_healing]` section to the RCH config file with fine-grained control over self-healing behaviors, plus environment variable and CLI overrides.

## Configuration Schema

### Config File Location
`~/.config/rch/config.toml` (existing config file)

### New Section
```toml
[self_healing]
# When hook fails to connect to daemon, try to start it automatically
# Default: true
# Env override: RCH_HOOK_STARTS_DAEMON=0|1
hook_starts_daemon = true

# When daemon starts, check and install Claude Code hook if missing
# Default: true
# Env override: RCH_DAEMON_INSTALLS_HOOKS=0|1
daemon_installs_hooks = true

# Maximum time (seconds) to wait for daemon to start before giving up
# Default: 3
# Env override: RCH_DAEMON_START_TIMEOUT=<seconds>
daemon_start_timeout = 3

# Minimum time (seconds) between auto-start attempts to prevent restart spam
# Default: 30
# Env override: RCH_AUTO_START_COOLDOWN=<seconds>
auto_start_cooldown = 30

# Log level for self-healing operations (debug, info, warn, error)
# Default: "info"
# Env override: RCH_SELF_HEALING_LOG_LEVEL=<level>
self_healing_log_level = "info"
```

## Implementation Plan

### 1. Add config struct
In `rch/src/config.rs`:

```rust
#[derive(Debug, Clone, Serialize, Deserialize)]
#[serde(default)]
pub struct SelfHealingConfig {
    /// When hook fails to connect to daemon, try to start it
    pub hook_starts_daemon: bool,

    /// When daemon starts, install Claude Code hook if missing
    pub daemon_installs_hooks: bool,

    /// Max seconds to wait for daemon to start
    pub daemon_start_timeout: u32,

    /// Min seconds between auto-start attempts
    pub auto_start_cooldown: u32,

    /// Log level for self-healing operations
    pub self_healing_log_level: String,
}

impl Default for SelfHealingConfig {
    fn default() -> Self {
        Self {
            hook_starts_daemon: true,
            daemon_installs_hooks: true,
            daemon_start_timeout: 3,
            auto_start_cooldown: 30,
            self_healing_log_level: "info".to_string(),
        }
    }
}

impl SelfHealingConfig {
    /// Apply environment variable overrides
    pub fn with_env_overrides(mut self) -> Self {
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_HOOK_STARTS_DAEMON") {
            self.hook_starts_daemon = val != "0" && val.to_lowercase() != "false";
        }
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_DAEMON_INSTALLS_HOOKS") {
            self.daemon_installs_hooks = val != "0" && val.to_lowercase() != "false";
        }
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_DAEMON_START_TIMEOUT") {
            if let Ok(secs) = val.parse() {
                self.daemon_start_timeout = secs;
            }
        }
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_AUTO_START_COOLDOWN") {
            if let Ok(secs) = val.parse() {
                self.auto_start_cooldown = secs;
            }
        }
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_SELF_HEALING_LOG_LEVEL") {
            self.self_healing_log_level = val;
        }
        // Master disable switch
        if let Ok(val) = std::env::var("RCH_NO_SELF_HEALING") {
            if val == "1" || val.to_lowercase() == "true" {
                self.hook_starts_daemon = false;
                self.daemon_installs_hooks = false;
            }
        }
        self
    }
}
```

